<div type="commentary" n="none">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>Line 2 is perhaps a name followed by τοῦ τέ [κνου but two names in a genealogy are also possible.</p><p> In line 3 the first letter might also be gamma, xi or tau; how the following letters should be divided is uncertain, bu tcf 1549 (= MAMA 556b), l. 3, ἕτερος δὲ οὐδείς· καί . . .  ,and no-one else (shall be buried there), and.</p><p>Line 4 might be from a version of the formula τῆς ἐπιγραφῆς ἀντίγραφον ἀπετέθη εἰς τὸ χρεοφυλάκιον - a copy of this inscription was deposited in the Property -archive.</p><p>Line 6 should be from the date for the relevant entry in the Property -archive.</p>
</div>
